description: Package Description
A framework intended to assist in the development of .Net framework web application.
summary:
This package contains dlls offering assistance building line of business apps by providing functionality addressing cross-cutting concerns, generic standard contract wcf services, restful webapi infrastructure, and data access support to several datastores.

The xf provides a generic standard contract service wherein a client simply makes a RESTful type call for any dto or business object, and the data access code is discovered and executed at runtime using MEF.  

The xf also includes three dlls to assist in building a robust RESTful webapi, where each api call may be logged (along with what code responded to the call).  Route handling controllers may be implemented as discoverable dlls, so that deployment may consist of simply adding dlls to a folder.

description:
This project is a convex hull algorithm and library for 2D,  3D, and higher dimensions. The code can also be used to compute Delaunay triangulations and Voronoi meshes of the input data. The benchmarks indicate that the convex hull code and 4 and higher dimensional triangulation code is on par or better than the solution provided by the C++ library CGAL.
The code is written in C# 4.0 and provides a template based API that allows extensive customization of the underlying types that represents vertices and faces of the convex hull. The algorithm itself is technically an implementation of the QuickHull algorithm. Nevertheless, it's not just a simple port of QHull as a different approach and data structures are used in the MIConvexHull algorithm.
summary: This project is a convex hull algorithm and library for 2D, 3D, and higher dimensions. The code can also be used to compute Delaunay triangulations and Voronoi meshes of the input data.
